function t.calculateGrassWeights() --[[ calculateGrassWeights | Line: 22 | Upvalues: GrassTypes (copy), t2 (copy), Data (copy), LethalNum (copy) ]]
    for k, v in pairs(GrassTypes.Types) do
        t2[k] = 0
    end

    local currentTier = Data.ImportantData.Stats.currentTier
    local tierUpRequirement = GrassTypes.Types[currentTier].tierUpRequirement
    local tierProgress = Data.ImportantData.Currencies.tierProgress

    if Data.ImportantData.Stats.pDif > 0 then
        tierProgress = LethalNum.copy(tierUpRequirement)
    end

    local v2 = LethalNum.toNumber(LethalNum.divide(tierProgress, tierUpRequirement))

    t2[currentTier] = 100 - v2 * 100
    t2[GrassTypes.Types[currentTier].nextTier] = v2 * 100
end
